Duchossois family to diversify investments


The Duchossois family is forming a new entity to separate its investment activities from its business operations, allowing the clan best-known for its horse racetrack holdings to further diversify its wealth and have quicker access to capital. The new Duchossois Capital Management LLC will absorb the family's other investment entities, including its technology investment arm, Duchossois Technology Partners, which invests in early-stage companies, and its Duchossois Capital Partners, which invests in smaller companies that are in a growth phase.The new company will be led by Richard Duchossois as chairman, his son Craig Duchossois as vice chairman and Michael Flannery as president, the company said in a statement."This is the family's desire to create more diversification and more potential liquidity," Mr. Flannery said in an interview. The new entity will allow the family to invest in some “smaller strategies," he said. Having the family's money tied up in major operating businesses sometimes makes the capital less available for other purposes, he said.Still, investments will be in sectors in which the family is already involved, such as consumer products, technology and transportation, he said. Real estate, publicly traded securities, leasing and private equity are all possible types of new investments, the statement said."We have been primarily focused on wholly owned operating businesses and, going forward, we'll look at a broader range of investments," Mr. Flannery said. "We don't need to necessarily own 100 percent of the asset."The enterprise provides a new executive perch for Mr. Flannery, 54, who has worked for the family for about 25 years, most recently as executive vice president and chief financial officer at Duchossois Group since 2005.To this point, the investment arms and four major companies owned by the family have all been run through Elmhurst-based Duchossois Group Inc., which is also the largest owner of the horse racetrack company Churchill Downs Inc. The management team for that company includes Richard as chairman, his son as CEO and Robert Fealy as president and chief operating officer. The biggest of Duchossois Group's wholly owned companies is garage door opener company Chamberlain Group Inc., also based in Elmhurst. The company has holdings valued at more than $2 billion, with about 5,000 employees in North America, Europe and Asia, according to the company's website.


Duchossois Industries Inc.
Craig J. Duchossois
Richard L. Duchossois
Consumer Products
Real Estate
Technology
Transportation
